Package ca.cgjennings.spelling

Class Suggestion

  • java.lang.Object
    • ca.cgjennings.spelling.Suggestion
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Comparable<Suggestion>
    public class Suggestion
extends Object
implements Comparable<Suggestion>
    This class groups a suggestion together with an estimate of its relevance. The Comparable implementation can be used to sort suggestions into their preferred order.

        public Suggestion​(String suggestion,
                  int freqScore,
                  int phoneticDist,
                  int typeDist,
                  int editDist)
        Creates a Suggestion using a default scoring mechanism.
        Parameters:
        suggestion - the suggestion word
        freqScore - the suggestion's frequency score
        phoneticDist - the edit distance between the word's and suggestion's phonetic hashes, or 0
        typeDist - the typist's edit distance between the word and suggestion, or 0
        editDist - the edit distance between the word and suggestion, or 0

      • getRelevance

        public int getRelevance()
        Returns an ordinal measure of how likely the spell checker thinks that this suggestion is relevant. A score of zero is maximally relevant, while increasing scores are increasingly less relevant.
        Returns:
        the relevance score for the suggestion
